nandgaon state (hindi: नांदगाँव), also known as raj nandgaon, was one of the princely states of india during the period of the british raj. nandgaon town, in present-day rajnandgaon district of chhattisgarh, was the only town of the state and the see of the ruler's residence. the first ruler ghasi das mahant, was recognized as a feudal chief by the british government in 1865 and was granted a sanad of adoption. later the british conferred the title of raja on the ruling mahant.